habitat_description: The distribution of the Texas ratsnake expands primarily west of the Mississippi River from southern Louisiana, southern and central Texas, Oklahoma, central and eastern Kansas, southeastern Nebraska, southeastern Iowa, and southeastern Minnesota (Brubrink 2001; Natureserve.org).
